  <Name>k__BackingField: Amos
  fancyName: 
  nickname: amo
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  This message was given to Amos, a shepherd from the town of Tekoa
        in Judah. He received this message in visions two years before the earthquake,
        when Uzziah was king of Judah and Jeroboam II, the son of Jehoash,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        was king of Israel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Joash, </b>a variant spelling of Jehoash.
    - title: "God\u2019s Judgment on Israel\u2019s Neighbors"
      content: "This is what he saw and heard:\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        voice will roar from Zionand thunder from Jerusalem!The lush pastures of
        the shepherds will dry up;the grass on Mount Carmel will wither and die.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CThe people
        of Damascus have sinned again and again,[[COMMENT(0)]]and I will not let
        them go unpunished!They beat down my people in Gileadas grain is threshed
        with iron sledges.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>have committed three sins, even four; </b>also in 1:6,
          9, 11, 13.
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send down fire on King Hazael\u2019s palace,and the fortresses
        of King Ben-hadad will be destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will break down the gates of Damascusand slaughter the people in
        the valley of Aven.I will destroy the ruler in Beth-eden,and the people of
        Aram will go as captives to Kir,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CThe people
        of Gaza have sinned again and again,and I will not let them go unpunished!They
        sent whole villages into exile,selling them as slaves to Edom.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I will send down fire on the walls of Gaza,and all its fortresses
        will be destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will slaughter the people of Ashdodand destroy the king of Ashkelon.Then
        I will turn to attack Ekron,and the few Philistines still left will be killed,\u201Dsays
        the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CThe people
        of Tyre have sinned again and again,and I will not let them go unpunished!They
        broke their treaty of brotherhood with Israel,selling whole villages as slaves
        to Edom.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send down fire on the walls of Tyre,and all its fortresses
        will be destroyed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CThe people
        of Edom have sinned again and again,and I will not let them go unpunished!They
        chased down their relatives, the Israelites, with swords,showing them no
        mercy.In their rage, they slashed them continuallyand were unrelenting in
        their anger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send down fire on Teman,and the fortresses of Bozrah will
        be destroyed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CThe people
        of Ammon have sinned again and again,and I will not let them go unpunished!When
        they attacked Gilead to extend their borders,they ripped open pregnant women
        with their swords.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I will send down fire on the walls of Rabbah,and all its fortresses
        will be destroyed.The battle will come upon them with shouts,like a whirlwind
        in a mighty storm.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CThe people
        of Moab have sinned again and again,[[COMMENT(0)]]and I will not let them
        go unpunished!They desecrated the bones of Edom\u2019s king,burning them
        to ashes.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>have committed three sins, even four; </b>also in 2:4,
          6.
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send down fire on the land of Moab,and all the fortresses
        in Kerioth will be destroyed.The people will fall in the noise of battle,as
        the warriors shout and the ram\u2019s horn sounds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "God\u2019s Judgment on Judah and Israel"
      content: "And I will destroy their kingand slaughter all their princes,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CThe people
        of Judah have sinned again and again,and I will not let them go unpunished!They
        have rejected the instruction of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,refusing
        to obey his decrees.They have been led astray by the same liesthat deceived
        their ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send down fire on Judah,and all the fortresses of Jerusalem
        will be destroyed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CThe people
        of Israel have sinned again and again,and I will not let them go unpunished!They
        sell honorable people for silverand poor people for a pair of sandals.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They trample helpless people in the dustand shove the oppressed out
        of the way.Both father and son sleep with the same woman,corrupting my holy
        name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At their religious festivals,they lounge in clothing their debtors
        put up as security.In the house of their gods,[[COMMENT(0)]]they drink wine
        bought with unjust fines.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:8 '
        content: Or <b>their God.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut as my people watched,I destroyed the Amorites,though they
        were as tall as cedarsand as strong as oaks.I destroyed the fruit on their
        branchesand dug out their roots.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It was I who rescued you from Egyptand led you through the desert
        for forty years,so you could possess the land of the Amorites.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I chose some of your sons to be prophetsand others to be Nazirites.Can
        you deny this, my people of Israel?\u201Dasks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you caused the Nazirites to sin by making them drink wine,and
        you commanded the prophets, \u2018Shut up!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo I will make you groanlike a wagon loaded down with sheaves
        of grain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your fastest runners will not get away.The strongest among you will
        become weak.Even mighty warriors will be unable to save themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The archers will not stand their ground.The swiftest runners won\u2019t
        be fast enough to escape.Even those riding horses won\u2019t be able to save
        themselves.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  Listen to this message that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        spoken against you, O people of Israel\u2014against the entire family I rescued
        from Egypt:  "
      comments: []
    - title: Witnesses against Guilty Israel
      content: "\u201CFrom among all the families on the earth,I have been intimate
        with you alone.That is why I must punish youfor all your sins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can two people walk togetherwithout agreeing on the direction?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Does a lion ever roar in a thicketwithout first finding a victim?Does
        a young lion growl in its denwithout first catching its prey?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Does a bird ever get caught in a trapthat has no bait?Does a trap
        spring shutwhen there\u2019s nothing to catch?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the ram\u2019s horn blows a warning,shouldn\u2019t the people
        be alarmed?Does disaster come to a cityunless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has planned it?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Indeed, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> never does anythinguntil
        he reveals his plans to his servants the prophets.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The lion has roared\u2014so who isn\u2019t frightened?The Sovereign
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken\u2014so who can refuse to proclaim
        his message?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Announce this to the leaders of Philistia[[COMMENT(0)]]and to the
        great ones of Egypt:\u201CTake your seats now on the hills around Samaria,and
        witness the chaos and oppression in Israel.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ashdod.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy people have forgotten how to do right,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CTheir
        fortresses are filled with wealthtaken by theft and violence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore,\u201D says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Can
        enemy is coming!He will surround them and shatter their defenses.Then he
        will plunder all their fortresses.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CA shepherd
        who tries to rescue a sheep from a lion\u2019s mouthwill recover only two
        legs or a piece of an ear.So it will be for the Israelites in Samaria lying
        on luxurious beds,and for the people of Damascus reclining on couches.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew in this sentence is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow listen to this, and announce it throughout all Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D
        says the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>the house of Jacob. </b>The names \u201CJacob\u201D and
          \u201CIsrael\u201D are often interchanged throughout the Old Testament,
          referring sometimes to the individual patriarch and sometimes to the nation."
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COn the very day I punish Israel for its sins,I will destroy
        the pagan altars at Bethel.The horns of the altar will be cut offand fall
        to the ground.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Israel\u2019s Failure to Learn"
      content: "  Listen to me, you fat cows[[COMMENT(0)]]living in Samaria,you women
        who oppress the poorand crush the needy,and who are always calling to your
        husbands,\u201CBring us another drink!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>you cows of Bashan.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sworn this by his holiness:\u201CThe
        time will come when you will be led awaywith hooks in your noses.Every last
        one of you will be dragged awaylike a fish on a hook!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will be led out through the ruins of the wall;you will be thrown
        from your fortresses,[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:3 '
        content: Or <b>thrown out toward Harmon, </b>possibly a reference to Mount
          Hermon.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo ahead and offer sacrifices to the idols at Bethel.Keep on
        disobeying at Gilgal.Offer sacrifices each morning,and bring your tithes
        every three days.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Present your bread made with yeastas an offering of thanksgiving.Then
        give your extra voluntary offeringsso you can brag about it everywhere!This
        is the kind of thing you Israelites love to do,\u201Dsays the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI brought hunger to every cityand famine to every town.But
        still you would not return to me,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI kept the rain from fallingwhen your crops needed it the most.I
        sent rain on one townbut withheld it from another.Rain fell on one field,while
        another field withered away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People staggered from town to town looking for water,but there was
        never enough.But still you would not return to me,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI struck your farms and vineyards with blight and mildew.Locusts
        devoured all your fig and olive trees.But still you would not return to me,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI sent plagues on youlike the plagues I sent on Egypt long
        ago.I killed your young men in warand led all your horses away.[[COMMENT(0)]]The
        stench of death filled the air!But still you would not return to me,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        content: Or <b>and slaughtered your captured horses.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI destroyed some of your cities,as I destroyed[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Sodom and Gomorrah.Those of you who survivedwere like charred sticks pulled
        from a fire.But still you would not return to me,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>as when God destroyed.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, I will bring upon you all the disasters I have announced.Prepare
        to meet your God in judgment, you people of Israel!\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Call to Repentance
      content: '  Listen, you people of Israel! Listen to this funeral song I am
        singing:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe virgin Israel has fallen,never to rise again!She lies abandoned
        on the ground,with no one to help her up.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CWhen a city
        sends a thousand men to battle,only a hundred will return.When a town sends
        a hundred,only ten will come back alive.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to the family
        of Israel:\u201CCome back to me and live!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t worship at the pagan altars at Bethel;don\u2019t go to
        the shrines at Gilgal or Beersheba.For the people of Gilgal will be dragged
        off into exile,and the people of Bethel will be reduced to nothing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come back to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and live!Otherwise,
        he will roar through Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] like a fire,devouring you completely.Your
        gods in Bethelwon\u2019t be able to quench the flames.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the house of Joseph.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You twist justice, making it a bitter pill for the oppressed.You
        treat the righteous like dirt.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who created the stars,the Pleiades
        and Orion.He turns darkness into morningand day into night.He draws up water
        from the oceansand pours it down as rain on the land.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is his name!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'With blinding speed and power he destroys the strong,crushing all
        their defenses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How you hate honest judges!How you despise people who tell the truth!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You trample the poor,stealing their grain through taxes and unfair
        rent.Therefore, though you build beautiful stone houses,you will never live
        in them.Though you plant lush vineyards,you will never drink wine from them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I know the vast number of your sinsand the depth of your rebellions.You
        oppress good people by taking bribesand deprive the poor of justice in the
        courts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So those who are smart keep their mouths shut,for it is an evil time.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do what is good and run from evilso that you may live!Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God of Heaven\u2019s Armies will be your helper,just as you have claimed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hate evil and love what is good;turn your courts into true halls
        of justice.Perhaps even yet the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s
        Armieswill have mercy on the remnant of his people.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the remnant of Joseph.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God of Heaven\u2019s Armies, says:\u201CThere will be crying in all the public
        squaresand mourning in every street.Call for the farmers to weep with you,and
        summon professional mourners to wail.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Warning of Coming Judgment
      content: "There will be wailing in every vineyard,for I will destroy them all,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What sorrow awaits you who say,\u201CIf only the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        were here!\u201DYou have no idea what you are wishing for.That day will bring
        darkness, not light.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day you will be like a man who runs from a lion\u2014only
        to meet a bear.Escaping from the bear, he leans his hand against a wall in
        his house\u2014and he\u2019s bitten by a snake.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be dark and
        hopeless,without a ray of joy or hope.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI hate all your show and pretense\u2014the hypocrisy of your
        religious festivals and solemn assemblies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will not accept your burnt offerings and grain offerings.I won\u2019t
        even notice all your choice peace offerings.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Away with your noisy hymns of praise!I will not listen to the music
        of your harps.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, I want to see a mighty flood of justice,an endless river
        of righteous living.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWas it to me you were bringing sacrifices and offerings during
        the forty years in the wilderness, Israel? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, you served your pagan gods\u2014Sakkuth your king god and Kaiwan
        your star god\u2014the images you made for yourselves. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  What sorrow awaits you who lounge in luxury in Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]]and
        you who feel secure in Samaria!You are famous and popular in Israel,and people
        go to you for help.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But go over to Calnehand see what happened there.Then go to the great
        city of Hamathand down to the Philistine city of Gath.You are no better than
        they were,and look at how they were destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You push away every thought of coming disaster,but your actions only
        bring the day of judgment closer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How terrible for you who sprawl on ivory bedsand lounge on your couches,eating
        the meat of tender lambs from the flockand of choice calves fattened in the
        stall.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You sing trivial songs to the sound of the harpand fancy yourselves
        to be great musicians like David.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You drink wine by the bowlfuland perfume yourselves with fragrant
        lotions.You care nothing about the ruin of your nation.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Joseph.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, you will be the first to be led away as captives.Suddenly,
        all your parties will end.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sworn by his own name,
        and this is what he, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, says:\u201CI despise the arrogance of Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]and I
        hate their fortresses.I will give this cityand everything in it to their
        enemies.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jacob. </b>See note on 3:13.
    - title: 
      content: '(If there are ten men left in one house, they will all die. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And when a relative who is responsible to dispose of the dead[[COMMENT(0)]]
        goes into the house to carry out the bodies, he will ask the last survivor,
        \u201CIs anyone else with you?\u201D When the person begins to swear, \u201CNo,
        by . . . ,\u201D he will interrupt and say, \u201CStop! Don\u2019t even mention
        the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D)  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:10 '
        content: Or <b>to burn the dead. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gives the command,homes both
        great and small will be smashed to pieces.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can horses gallop over boulders?Can oxen be used to plow them?But
        that\u2019s how foolish you are when you turn justice into poisonand the
        sweet fruit of righteousness into bitterness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And you brag about your conquest of Lo-debar.[[COMMENT(0)]]You boast,
        \u201CDidn\u2019t we take Karnaim[[COMMENT(1)]] by our own strength?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:13a '
        content: "<b>Lo-debar </b>means \u201Cnothing.\u201D"
      - number: '6:13b '
        content: "<b>Karnaim </b>means \u201Chorns,\u201D a term that symbolizes
          strength."
  - verses:
    - title: A Vision of Locusts
      content: "  The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> showed me a vision. I
        saw him preparing to send a vast swarm of locusts over the land. This was
        after the king\u2019s share had been harvested from the fields and as the
        main crop was coming up. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In my vision the locusts ate every green plant in sight. Then I said,
        \u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, please forgive us or we will
        not survive, for Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] is so small.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jacob; </b>also in 7:5. See note on 3:13.
    - title: A Vision of Fire
      content: "So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> relented from this plan. \u201CI
        will not do it,\u201D he said.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> showed me another
        vision. I saw him preparing to punish his people with a great fire. The fire
        had burned up the depths of the sea and was devouring the entire land. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said, \u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, please
        stop or we will not survive, for Israel is so small.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Vision of a Plumb Line
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> relented from this plan, too.
        \u201CI will not do that either,\u201D said the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then he showed me another vision. I saw the Lord standing beside
        a wall that had been built using a plumb line. He was using a plumb line
        to see if it was still straight. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CAmos, what
        do you see?\u201DI answered, \u201CA plumb line.\u201DAnd the Lord replied,
        \u201CI will test my people with this plumb line. I will no longer ignore
        all their sins. "
      comments: []
    - title: Amos and Amaziah
      content: "The pagan shrines of your ancestors[[COMMENT(0)]] will be ruined,
        and the temples of Israel will be destroyed; I will bring the dynasty of
        King Jeroboam to a sudden end.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Isaac.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then Amaziah, the priest of Bethel, sent a message to Jeroboam, king
        of Israel: \u201CAmos is hatching a plot against you right here on your very
        doorstep! What he is saying is intolerable. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He is saying, \u2018Jeroboam will soon be killed, and the people
        of Israel will be sent away into exile.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Amaziah sent orders to Amos: \u201CGet out of here, you prophet!
        Go on back to the land of Judah, and earn your living by prophesying there! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t bother us with your prophecies here in Bethel. This is
        the king\u2019s sanctuary and the national place of worship!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Amos replied, \u201CI\u2019m not a professional prophet, and
        I was never trained to be one.[[COMMENT(0)]] I\u2019m just a shepherd, and
        I take care of sycamore-fig trees. "
      comments:
      - number: '7:14 '
        content: "Or <b>I\u2019m not a prophet nor the son of a prophet.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> called me away from my flock
        and told me, \u2018Go and prophesy to my people in Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now then, listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CYou
        say,\u2018Don\u2019t prophesy against Israel.Stop preaching against my people.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>against the house of Isaac.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: A Vision of Ripe Fruit
      content: '  Then the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> showed me another
        vision. In it I saw a basket filled with ripe fruit. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat do you see, Amos?\u201D he asked.I replied, \u201CA basket
        full of ripe fruit.\u201DThen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CLike
        this fruit, Israel is ripe for punishment! I will not delay their punishment
        again. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day the singing in the temple will turn to wailing. Dead
        bodies will be scattered everywhere. They will be carried out of the city
        in silence. I, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen to this, you who rob the poorand trample down the needy!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You can\u2019t wait for the Sabbath day to be overand the religious
        festivals to endso you can get back to cheating the helpless.You measure
        out grain with dishonest measuresand cheat the buyer with dishonest scales.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>You make the ephah </b>[a unit for measuring grain] <b>small
          and the shekel </b>[a unit of weight] <b>great, and you deal falsely by
          using deceitful balances.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'And you mix the grain you sellwith chaff swept from the floor.Then
        you enslave poor peoplefor one piece of silver or a pair of sandals.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sworn this oathby his own
        name, the Pride of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]]:\u201CI will never forgetthe wicked
        things you have done!  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the pride of Jacob. </b>See note on 3:13.
    - title: 
      content: 'The earth will tremble for your deeds,and everyone will mourn.The
        ground will rise like the Nile River at floodtime;it will heave up, then
        sink again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn that day,\u201D says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201CI
        will make the sun go down at noonand darken the earth while it is still day.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will turn your celebrations into times of mourningand your singing
        into weeping.You will wear funeral clothesand shave your heads to show your
        sorrow\u2014as if your only son had died.How very bitter that day will be!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe time is surely coming,\u201D says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cwhen
        I will send a famine on the land\u2014not a famine of bread or waterbut of
        hearing the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People will stagger from sea to seaand wander from border to border[[COMMENT(0)]]searching
        for the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,but they will not find it.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>from north to east.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Beautiful girls and strong young menwill grow faint in that day,thirsting
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s word.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Vision of God at the Altar
      content: "  Then I saw a vision of the Lord standing beside the altar. He said,\u201CStrike
        the tops of the Temple columns,so that the foundation will shake.Bring down
        the roofon the heads of the people below.I will kill with the sword those
        who survive.No one will escape!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEven if they dig down to the place of the dead,[[COMMENT(0)]]I
        will reach down and pull them up.Even if they climb up into the heavens,I
        will bring them down.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Even if they hide at the very top of Mount Carmel,I will search them
        out and capture them.Even if they hide at the bottom of the ocean,I will
        send the sea serpent after them to bite them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even if their enemies drive them into exile,I will command the sword
        to kill them there.I am determined to bring disaster upon themand not to
        help them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,touches
        the land and it melts,and all its people mourn.The ground rises like the
        Nile River at floodtime,and then it sinks again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s home reaches up to the heavens,while
        its foundation is on the earth.He draws up water from the oceansand pours
        it down as rain on the land.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is his name!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAre you Israelites more important to methan the Ethiopians?[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D
        asks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CI brought Israel out of Egypt,but
        I also brought the Philistines from Crete[[COMMENT(1)]]and led the Arameans
        out of Kir.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:7a '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Cushites?</b>
      - number: '9:7b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Caphtor.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,am watching this
        sinful nation of Israel.I will destroy itfrom the face of the earth.But I
        will never completely destroy the family of Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the house of Jacob. </b>See note on 3:13.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor I will give the commandand will shake Israel along with
        the other nationsas grain is shaken in a sieve,yet not one true kernel will
        be lost.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Promise of Restoration
      content: "But all the sinners will die by the sword\u2014all those who say,
        \u2018Nothing bad will happen to us.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn that day I will restore the fallen house[[COMMENT(0)]] of
        David.I will repair its damaged walls.From the ruins I will rebuild itand
        restore its former glory.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:11a '
        content: Or <b>kingdom; </b>Hebrew reads <b>tent.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "And Israel will possess what is left of Edomand all the nations I
        have called to be mine.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201DThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken,and he will do these things.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:11b-12 '
        content: "Greek version reads <b>and restore its former glory, / so that
          the rest of humanity, including the Gentiles\u2014 / all those I have called
          to be mine\u2014might seek me. </b>Compare Acts 15:16-17."
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe time will come,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cwhen
        the grain and grapes will grow fasterthan they can be harvested.Then the
        terraced vineyards on the hills of Israelwill drip with sweet wine!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will bring my exiled people of Israelback from distant lands,and
        they will rebuild their ruined citiesand live in them again.They will plant
        vineyards and gardens;they will eat their crops and drink their wine.  '
      comments: []
